type="local"
href="marcelofiore.xml"
addr="marcelofiore"
title="Marcelo Fiore">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link></fr:contributor></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KF.xml"
addr="jms-00KF"
title="Function">function</fr:link> <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> is said to be <fr:em><fr:strong>injective</fr:strong></fr:em>, or an <fr:em><fr:strong>injection</fr:strong></fr:em>, whenever we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\forall  a_1,a_2\in  A\mathpunct {.} f{\mathopen {}\left (a_1\right )\mathclose {}}=f{\mathopen {}\left (a_2\right )\mathclose {}}\implies  a_1=a_2]]></fr:tex>. Such a <fr:link
type="local"
href="jms-00KF.xml"
addr="jms-00KF"
title="Function">function</fr:link> is written <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\rightarrowtail  B]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree><fr:tree
